{"lemma":"بالِ","slug":"بالِ","root":"ب.#.ل","root_slug":"ب-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بال","root":"بول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3297","n3564","n3569"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mind, state"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attention, mindfulness, heed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to urinate"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"worn out"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"It is explained as reanalysis of بَاءَ لِي (bāʔa lī, “it has come upon me”); predating Arabic literature by a millennium at least since there is Biblical Aramaic בָּל (bāl, “mind, heed”).\n\nDenominal verb of بَوْل (bawl, “urine”), itself related by metathesis, univerbation, or another process happening before the record of Arabic, to وَبْل (wabl, “a heavy, large-dropped rain”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of بَلِيَ (baliya, “to wear out”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/baːl/","/baː.la/","/boːl/","/baː.lin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3297","headword_ar":"بَالٍ","root":"blw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAhu","text_ar":"بَلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trying, proving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"testing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  And hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being acquainted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with a thing]; as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalotuhu","text_ar":"جَعَلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAliyFA biEu*oriY","text_ar":"بَالِيًا بِعُذْرِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him to be acquainted with my excuse, and to know the manner thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old, and wearing out"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn out"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; applied to a garment. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAliyaAtN","text_ar":"بَالِيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places of tents."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 492.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3564","headword_ar":"بَالَ","root":"bwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabuwlu","text_ar":"يَبُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawolN","text_ar":"بَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabaAlN","text_ar":"مَبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He urined, discharged his urine, made water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of a man, (M, Msb,) and of a beast, (Msb,) &c. (M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAla bawolFA $ariyfFA faAxirFA","text_ar":"بَالَ بَوْلًا شَرِيفًا فَاخِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"begat offspring resembling him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Mufaddal, T, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in form and natural dispositions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Mufaddal, TA.) ―         -b3-  A poet, using the verb metaphorically, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"baAla suhayolN fiY AlfaDiyxi fafasado"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Canopus made water in the beverage prepared from unripe dates, and it became spoiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marred"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) meaning, that when Canopus"},{"kind":"page_break","n":277},{"kind":"text","text":"rises [aurorally, which it does, in central Arabia, early in August, the making of that beverage is stopped, for] the season of unripe dates has passed, and they have become ripe. (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDx","text_ar":"فضخ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAla suhayolN","text_ar":"بَالَ سُهَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a prov., said when winter has come. (MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrt","text_ar":"خرت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suhayolN","text_ar":"سُهَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawolN","text_ar":"بَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having vent, so as to flow forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baw~aAlN","text_ar":"بَوَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a wine-skin: see this word below. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAla","text_ar":"بَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It melted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissolved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) said of fat. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n3569","headword_ar":"بَالٌ","root":"bwl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^onN","text_ar":"شَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, for which one cares;"},{"kind":"text","text":"wherefore one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baAlayotu bika*aA","text_ar":"مَا بَالَيْتُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlapN","text_ar":"بَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ I cared not for such a thing: ” (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which one cares:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 94:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAlu","text_ar":"البَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlu Aln~afosi","text_ar":"بَالُ النَّفْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"care,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concern;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence is [said to be] derived"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlayotu","text_ar":"بَالَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", having for its inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlapN","text_ar":"بَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baAluka","text_ar":"مَا بَالُكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is thy state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See the Kur xii. 50 and xx. 53: and see an ex. in a verse cited in this Lex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] When it was said to a man, in former times, “ How hast thou entered upon the morning? ” he used to reply,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bixayorK A^aSolaHa A@ll~`hu baAlakumo","text_ar":"بِخَيْرٍ اَصْلَحَ ا@للّٰهُ بَالَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With good fortune: may God make good your state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 77.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa yuSoliHu baAlahumo","text_ar":"وَ يُصْلِحُ بَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xlvii. 6], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And He will make good their state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, in the present world:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their means of subsistence in the present world, together with their recompense in the world to come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa raxiY~u","text_ar":"هُوَ رَخِىُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAli","text_ar":"البَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in ample and easy circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is not straitened in circumstances, nor troubled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is in an easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pleasant, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rxw","text_ar":"رخو"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unstraitened, in mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAlu","text_ar":"البَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaA='u AlbaAli","text_ar":"رَخَا=ءُ البَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness and easiness of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbAl","text_ar":"البال"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unstraitened, state of the mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kaAsifu","text_ar":"هُوَ كَاسِفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAli","text_ar":"البَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in an evil state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is straitened in his hope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expectation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbAl","text_ar":"البال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expectation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) so says El-Hawaázinee. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa","text_ar":"لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mino baAliY","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِنْ بَالِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is not of the things for which I care."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u A^amorK *iY","text_ar":"كُلُّ اَمْرٍ ذِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlK lamo yubodaA^o fiyhi biHamodi A@ll~`hi fahuwa A^abotaru","text_ar":"بَالٍ لَمْ يُبْدَاْ فِيهِ بِحَمْدِ ا@للّٰهِ فَهُوَ اَبْتَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every honourable affair, for which one cares, and by which one is rendered solicitous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which a beginning is not made by praising God, is cut off from good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every affair of importance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in two places in this art.) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobN","text_ar":"قَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaladN","text_ar":"خَلَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ham pp. 76 and 77,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaATirN","text_ar":"خَاطِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, Kull p. 179.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTara bibaAliY","text_ar":"خَطَرَ بِبَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, Kull ubi suprà,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY baAliY","text_ar":"عَلَى بَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kull ibid.,) i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an affair, or a thing, Kull)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occurred to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bestirred itself in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, Kull.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yaxoTuro bibaAliY *`lika AlA^amoru","text_ar":"لَمْ يَخْطُرْ بِبَالِى ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That affair did not occur to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not move me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yaxoTuru fulaAnN bibaAliY","text_ar":"مَا يَخْطُرُ فُلَانٌ بِبَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does not occur to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"move,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attention."},{"kind":"text","text":"You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTiniY baAlaka","text_ar":"اَعْطِنِى بَالَكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give me thy mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attention."},{"kind":"text","text":"And]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^uloqiY A_ilayohi baAlFA","text_ar":"لَا اُلْقِى اـِلَيْهِ بَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I do not, give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pay, any attention to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Z, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blw","text_ar":"بلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whale;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great fish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fish of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHor","text_ar":"بَحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bulky fish, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalu AlbaHoru","text_ar":"جَمَلُ البَحْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fish fifty cubits long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) [Kzw describes it as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from four hundred to five hundred cubits in length,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it sometimes shows the extremity of its fin, like a great sail, and its head also, and blows forth water rising into the air higher than an arrow can be shot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"these and other exaggerated particulars he mentions in his account of the Sea of the Zenj: and in a later place he says, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it eats ambergris, and dies in consequence; and a great quantity of oil is procured from its brain, and used for lamps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the word [in this sense] is not Arabic: (S:) in the O it is said to be arabicized, from [the Persian]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlo","text_ar":"وَالْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spade"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~","text_ar":"مَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~","text_ar":"مُرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one works in land of seed-produce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlapN","text_ar":"بَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["T","S","Msb","K","TA","M","AZ","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}